## 3. Pricing and Feature Gates

Users must receive product value (a working bot response) before encountering paywall restrictions that block production deployment.

### Plans

| | **Free** | **Pro — $14.99/mo** | **Business — $29.99/mo** |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Bots | 1 | 1 | Up to 5 |
| Documents | 5 | 50 | Unlimited |
| Messages / month | 1,000 | 20,000 | 100,000 |
| Embed widget | Yes, with watermark | Yes, no watermark | Yes, no watermark |
| Custom branding | No | Colors, logo, welcome message | Above + custom domain |
| Analytics | No | Conversations, top questions | Above + export, team dashboard |
| Team seats | 1 | 1 | Up to 5 |
| API access | No | No | Yes |
| Suggested questions | 3 | Unlimited | Unlimited |
| Support | Community | Email | Priority |

Annual billing displays a 20% discount (UI only in prototype).

The Free plan is permanent. Sign-up does not require a credit card.

### Gated Actions and Paywall Triggers

| Trigger | Free limit | Required plan | Screen |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Upload 6th document | 5 documents max | Pro | Knowledge / Upload |
| Copy embed without watermark | Watermark in snippet | Pro | Deploy |
| Customize widget colors or logo | Settings locked | Pro | Widget Builder |
| View analytics | Empty or blurred state | Pro | Analytics |
| Create second bot | 1 bot max | Business | Dashboard |
| Invite teammate | Single user only | Business | Settings → Team |
| Generate API key | Not available | Business | Settings → API |
| Exceed monthly message limit | 1,000 messages | Pro or Business | Chat / Widget |

### Paywall Behavior

1. Do not surface the paywall before the aha moment: the user must upload documents and receive at least one meaningful response in test chat.
2. Use contextual prompts (inline banner, disabled control with upgrade tooltip). Do not block the landing page with a full-screen paywall.
3. Show the cost of staying on Free: side-by-side widget preview with and without watermark; explicit copy: *Your embed will show "Powered by EmbedKit".*
4. Upgrade is a deliberate choice after value is demonstrated, not a sign-up gate.

