## 4. Onboarding Flow

```
Landing → Sign Up → Create Bot → Upload Docs → Test Chat → Customize Widget → Embed Code → Paywall (on gated action)
```

### Step Definition

| Step | Screen | Objective | Required elements |
| :---: | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| 1 | Landing | Communicate value; drive sign-up | Hero, primary CTA ("Build your bot free"), social proof, three-step explainer, pricing summary |
| 2 | Sign Up | Minimize registration friction | Email and Google auth; no credit card |
| 3 | Create Bot | Establish bot context | Bot name, optional avatar; default name derived from company name |
| 4 | Upload Docs | Prepare knowledge base | Drag-and-drop PDF/TXT/DOCX; processing status; empty state with examples |
| 5 | Test Chat | Aha moment | ChatGPT-style interface; suggested questions; citation chips on responses |
| 6 | Widget Builder | Visual configuration | Live preview; color picker and welcome message (partially gated on Free) |
| 7 | Deploy | Activation | Copy `<script>` snippet; site preview; watermark notice on Free |
| 8 | Paywall | Conversion | Triggered on Pro/Business action; plan comparison |

### Empty States

| State | Copy / behavior |
| :--- | :--- |
| No documents uploaded | *Drop your FAQ, pricing page, or onboarding guide — we'll turn it into answers.* |
| Documents ready, no messages sent | Three clickable suggested questions derived from uploaded content |
| Embed copied on Free plan | Toast: *Widget live! Upgrade to remove EmbedKit branding.* |

### Time to Value

Target: **under 5 minutes** from sign-up to first bot response in test chat. Prototype uses mocked responses with realistic delay.

